# Vendly Comprehensive Technical Handover Guide

This document provides a detailed state-of-the-project report for the Vendly monorepo.

---

## 🟢 Frontend Progress (Next.js / Tailwind v4)

### 1. Foundation & Theming
- **Global Design System**: Managed in [vendly-web/app/globals.css](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/globals.css). Uses Tailwind v4 with scoped CSS variables (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--secondary`).
- **Persistent Theming**:
    - [components/theme-provider.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/components/theme-provider.tsx): Manages light/dark mode with `localStorage`.
    - [app/layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/layout.tsx): Uses `next/script` with `strategy="beforeInteractive"` to inject a theme-initialization script, preventing the Flash of Unstyled Content (FOUC).
- **Typography**: Standardized on **Nunito** for a friendly yet professional brand voice. Fluid scaling is used in the Landing Page hero.

### 2. Core Pages
- **Landing Page ([app/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/page.tsx))**:
    - Redesigned for "Stripe-polish" minimalist aesthetic.
    - Features a centered hero section, feature grid with high-precision rhythmic spacing, and a responsive footer.
    - Fully theme-aware (no hardcoded hex colors that break in dark mode).
- **Onboarding Wizard ([app/onboarding/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/onboarding/page.tsx))**:
    - A client-side multi-step state machine.
    - **Step 1**: Store Details (Name, Category, Location).
    - **Step 2**: Bot Persona (Personality selection and custom instructions).
    - **Step 3**: Channel Integration (Telegram Bot Token entry).
    - **Step 4**: Finalization and dashboard redirect.
- **Dashboard Infrastructure**:
    - [app/dashboard/layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/dashboard/layout.tsx): High-fidelity sidebar and header system.
    - [app/dashboard/ai/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/dashboard/ai/page.tsx): Advanced AI configuration UI with real-time preview simulation.
    - [app/dashboard/inventory/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/dashboard/inventory/page.tsx): Product management table with variant support.

---

## 🔵 Backend Progress (FastAPI / Prisma)

### 1. API Architecture
- **Standardized Responses**: Controlled in [app/schemas/responses.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/responses.py). Every functional endpoint returns a `Response[T]` object, ensuring the frontend always receives a consistent `{ success, message, data, error }` structure.
- **Authentication Flow**:
    - [core/security.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/core/security.py): Uses `pbkdf2_sha256` for robust hashing.
    - [app/api/v1/endpoints/auth.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/auth.py): Implements a standard-compliant `/login` that works seamlessly with Swagger's "Authorize" button.
    - [api/deps.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/deps.py): Exports [get_current_active_vendor](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/deps.py#34-39) for secure route protection.

### 2. Services & Data
- **AI Service ([app/services/ai_service.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/services/ai_service.py))**:
    - Integrates with **Groq (Llama-3)** via `httpx`.
    - Features a dynamic system prompt builder that injects vendor personality and store context into every chat.
    - Supports message history management.
- **Database Schema ([prisma/schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/prisma/schema.prisma))**:
    - Modelled for scale: [Vendor](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/vendor.py#24-35), [Product](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/product.py#47-56), [Order](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/order.py#16-26), [Transaction](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/transaction.py#14-21), [Coupon](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/coupon.py#16-23), [ChatMessage](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/chat.py#9-14), and [ChatSession](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/chat.py#21-30).
    - Uses `Decimal` types for financial accuracy and standard relationships (e.g., Product -> Image, Order -> Product).
- **Functional Endpoints**:
    - [endpoints/products.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/products.py): Multi-variant product support with image handling.
    - [endpoints/orders.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/orders.py): Standardized order creation and tracking.
    - [endpoints/ai.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/ai.py): REST endpoint for chat interactions, aligned with the [ChatResponse](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/chat.py#30-32) schema.

---

## 🛠 Infrastructure & Tooling
- **Monorepo**: Keeps frontend and backend logic close, facilitating shared schema understanding.
- **Prisma**: Python client used for type-safe database interactions.
- **Interswitch**: Basic structure for payment verification is in place within [transactions.py](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/transactions.py).

## 🚀 Next Technical Todos
1. **Webhook Processing**: Implement the logic in `handlers/` to handle incoming JSON payloads from Telegram/WhatsApp and route them to `ai_service`.
2. **Real-time Inventory**: Sync the [Inventory](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/vendly-web/app/dashboard/inventory/page.tsx#6-103) page with `prisma.product` updates via SWR or React Query.
3. **Payment Callbacks**: Connect the [Transaction](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/transaction.py#14-21) update logic to the Interswitch webhook endpoint once Sandbox credentials are fully live.

## 📝 Critical Implementation Notes
- **Theme Consistency**: Always use `bg-background` and `text-foreground` instead of `bg-white` or `bg-black`.
- **API Wrapping**: When adding new endpoints, always return [Response(data=...)](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/app/schemas/responses.py#6-11) to maintain frontend compatibility.
- **Prisma Generation**: If you change the [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Users/use/reactapps/vendly/backend/prisma/schema.prisma), remember to run `prisma generate` in the `backend` folder and restart the server.
